RACE.RACE_TEXT: OAKLAWN PARK RACE 12 1 3/4M Dirt CR: 102. Starter Allowance Purse 125000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $10,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since March 6, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since February 6, 2 023 Allowed 4 lbs. (Horses Which Have Never Won A Race At A Mile Or Over Allowed 3 lbs.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HELLORHIGHWATER close from the start, took over past the wire the first time, continued to show the way, drew out through the lane, under steady handling. TIGER MOON never far back outside, closer into the third turn, could do nothing with the winner in the drive, no match for the winner. NEPAL UP raced back, continued to race mid pack into the far turn, rallied outside, finished up best of the rest. POLTERER bothered at the break, was straightened, forwardly placed, chased the middle three quarters, had little left for the stretch. MOLIERE void of early foot, improved position without posing a serious threat. BACKGATE RED void of early foot, continued to lag, also improved position while also never dangerous. MULBERRY STREET one paced throughout through in lacking a closing response. FETCHS BRAHM in mid pack early, retreated after a mile. GOLD BUCKLE was finished after a half. BACK BEAT bothered, off a step slow, used to move up to contest the pace, stopped, distanced after losing contact with the field. GENERATOR finished early, far back, distanced.
